  "description": "Karl Witus Johansson was a Swedish editor known for his work in Värnamo Nyheter newspaper. He was born on April 13, 1895, in Svenarum, Jönköping County, to Viktor J. and Mathilda Svensdotter. He married Ruth Karlsson in 1924 and had two children with her. Johansson was a member of the Swedish Journalists Association and participated in several study trips sponsored by different organizations. He worked at the Jönköping County Forestry Board from 1917-1921 while also doing freelance work for the press. He later became the editor of Värnamo-Bladet from 1922-1930 before starting Värnamo Nyheter, where he served as chief editor, responsible publisher, and managing director. Apart from that, he was a member of the board for the Värnamo Home Society and a board member of the Swedish Newspaper Publishers Association. He wrote about local culture and community heritage and had an interest in traveling and studying local forestry. He retired as a member of the Jönköping County Forestry Board in 1932."
